if your goal is to cause harm & devastation to a community you do not belong to, do not come here. You are not welcome in Tulsa.

retweeted_text: Now bolstered by Trump's panning of the House Democrats' coronavirus bill, some Republicans are calling on Pelosi to call off the chamber's recess next week and keep working to find agreement on the measure.

full_text: Today, I wrote a letter to @SpeakerPelosi urging her to keep Congress in session until we have a coronavirus bill that can be passed by the Senate and signed by @realDonaldTrump into law. My letter is linked here: https://t.co/VFWcWYo49o

Flashback to 2009, when a Democrat-controlled Congress/White House passed a clean funding bill to combat H1N1 (swine flu). The vaccine cost $10.
 
The 2009 model worked. We didn't need big government price controls then, and we don't need them now.

Capitalism and free-market principles have driven our country to the forefront in worldwide innovation, exceptionalism, and leadership. 

These free-market principles are the only way to keep health care costs affordable.

full_text: The women of Oklahoma had the right to vote almost a full 2 years before the 19th Amendment passed Congress, making Oklahoma the 1st southern state to adopt full suffrage for women.

full_text:

retweeted_text:
Today, I joined @repkevinhern in sending a letter to @SecretarySonny, supporting the proposed rule to enforce work requirements for SNAP benefits. Food stamps should support families through difficulties, not become a way of life.

Read our full letter ‚û°Ô∏è https://t.co/2Rq5IeEG0K

full_text:
I sent a letter to @SecretarySonny today in support of @USDA proposed rule to enforce work requirements for able-bodied adults to get #SNAP benefits. 64 colleagues joined me.

You can read the full letter here: https://t.co/Vkcr02rAY0
